Analysis: Google Search Interest in Immigration-Related Topics vs Electoral Swing Per County

Dowland Aiello, Roy Lin, Winston Qi

2025-06-08

1. Overview

Herein, we explore the relationship between google search query frequency for topics related to immigration and the electoral swing in the Presidential election at a given point in time. We are particularly interested in the relationship between the change in search frequency and the magnitude of the electoral swinng.

2. Data Cleaning

See the scripts/ folder for utilities we wrote to clean our data. Notably, Google trends data for city / region over varying time frames were combined from multiple CSV files into a single table, which looks like this:

votestimeframe <- electiondf %>%
  select(year, state, county_name, party, office, candidatevotes, totalvotes) %>%
  # Only get rows where the candidates won
  group_by(year, state, county_name, office) %>%
  filter(candidatevotes == max(candidatevotes)) %>%
  ungroup %>%
  # Collapse votes in 2004 and 2008 into columns 2004 and 2008
  group_by(state, county_name, office) %>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols = c(state, county_name, party, office), names_from = year, values_from = c(candidatevotes, totalvotes))

4. Generic Function

Now, we make a reusable function which calculates the change over a given time period for all regions.

change_time_period <- function(date1, date2) {
  trendsdf %>%
  pivot_wider(id_cols = c(Region, City, DMA), names_from = daterange, values_from = query_incidence, values_fn = max) %>%
  (\(df) df %>% mutate("change_query_incidence" = df[[date1]] - df[[date2]]))
}

change_time_period("08-12", "04-08") %>% head(10)

#with_lat_long %>% head(10)

get_local_slope <- function(df, row_number, n = 5) {
  # Assumes df is sorted by lat, long
  below <- df[max(c(1, row_number - (n %/% 2))):row_number, ]
  above <- df[row_number:min(c((row_number + n / 2), nrow(df))), ]
  all = rbind(below, above)

  model <- lm(swing ~ change_query_incidence, data = all)
  coef(model)[["change_query_incidence"]]
}

with_lat_long <- read.csv("../../data_cleaned/swing_interest_vs_electoral_04_12_lat_long.csv") %>%
    mutate(lat = lat_long.lat, long = lat_long.lon) %>%
    arrange(lat, long)
with_corr <- with_lat_long %>%
    filter(!is.na(change_query_incidence) & !is.na(swing)) %>%
    (\(df) df %>% mutate(local_slope = (1:nrow(df)) %>% map(\(row_num) get_local_slope(df, row_num))))
with_corr %>% select(change_query_incidence, swing, local_slope, lat, long) %>% head(10)
